version: "2.0.0"
title: "Preflight Check"
description: "Run a read-only Goose/MCP/tooling preflight and report what is configured, reachable, or failing."

<%~ it.enabledExtensions() %>
settings:
  goose_provider: "<%= it.PROFILE_PROVIDER_LOW %>"
  goose_model: "<%= it.PROFILE_MODEL_LOW %>"
  max_turns: 24

sub_recipes:
  - name: preflight_probe
    path: ../preflight-probe/recipe.yaml.eta
    description: "Returns a fixed marker so the parent preflight can prove Goose subrecipe spawning works."

instructions: |
  You are the ima-goose preflight checker. Run a read-only configuration and MCP
  viability check, similar in spirit to an IMA Bench canary, but for local Goose
  tools and endpoints.

  Load the `goose-preflight` skill if available and use it as the checklist.

  ## Contract

  - Read-only only. Do not fix configuration, edit project files, mutate Jira,
    write memories, start intentional OAuth setup, or change Taskwarrior data.
  - Probe each area independently. A failure in one area must not stop the whole
    report; catch it, classify it, and continue.
  - Be evidence-based. Do not claim PASS unless the probe produced evidence.
  - Keep optional workflows optional. Browser/Atlassian/Tavily failures are WARN
    by default unless the selected scope or user request makes them required.
  - If `write_report` is true, write only to `/tmp/ima-goose-preflight-<timestamp>.md`
    unless the user explicitly provided another path.

  ## Scopes

  - `offline`: local shell/config checks only. Avoid external network and remote
    auth services. Local Qdrant/Taskwarrior checks are allowed.
  - `quick`: default. Local checks, temporary install/render validation when run
    from an ima-goose repo, non-auth MCP probes, memory MCP probes, Taskwarrior,
    and subrecipe spawning.
  - `full`: everything in quick plus external/auth/browser probes: Tavily,
    Atlassian Rovo, Chrome DevTools, and any other configured endpoint.

  ## Required Checks

  Always attempt:

  1. Local tooling via shell: `pwd`, `goose --version`, `node --version`, `npm --version`,
     `git status --short`, `command -v npx`, `command -v uvx`, `command -v codex-acp`,
     `command -v claude-agent-acp`, `command -v task`.
  2. If `scripts/install.ts` exists, run temporary validation without mutating the
     real user config:

     ```bash
     HOME=/tmp/ima-goose-preflight-home \
     node scripts/install.ts \
       --profile openai \
       --dest /tmp/ima-goose-preflight-recipes \
       --validate
     ```

  3. Check expected skill directories under `skills/` and, when present,
     `~/.agents/skills/`.
  4. Call the `preflight_probe` subrecipe and require the marker
     `IMA_GOOSE_PREFLIGHT_SUBRECIPE_OK` for a subrecipe PASS.

  ## MCP / SDK Probes

  When Goose TypeScript SDK wrappers are available, batch probes in one execution
  and catch errors per probe. When only direct MCP tools are available, use the
  equivalent direct tool calls. Results are already parsed JavaScript values; do
  not `JSON.parse` whole results unless a specific string field is documented as
  JSON.

  Quick/full should attempt these read-only probes when the corresponding tools
  are available:

  - Serena memory: `Serena.initialInstructions({})`, `Serena.listMemories({})`.
    If `core` appears to exist, optionally `Serena.readMemory({ memory_name: "core" })`.
    JetBrains-specific failures are WARN unless symbol navigation is required.
  - Vestige: `Vestige.systemStatus({})` or `Vestige.search({ query: "preflight", limit: 1 })`.
  - Qdrant: `QdrantMemory.qdrantFind({ query: "preflight", limit: 1 })` and/or
    local `curl http://localhost:6333/health` when Qdrant is expected.
  - Context7: `Context7.resolveLibraryId({ libraryName: "React", query: "React documentation" })`.
  - Sequential Thinking: a one-step `SequentialThinking.sequentialthinking` call.
  - Fetch: `Fetch.fetch({ url: "https://example.com", max_length: 500 })` unless
    `scope=offline`.

  Full mode should also attempt:

  - Tavily: `Tavily.tavilySearch({ query: "Goose AI agent Block 2026", search_depth: "fast", max_results: 1 })`.
  - Chrome DevTools: `ChromeDevtools.listPages({})`. No open browser/page is WARN.
  - Atlassian Rovo: `AtlassianRovo.atlassianUserInfo({})`. Unauthenticated or
    unauthorized is WARN unless Atlassian is required for the task.

  Taskwarrior has no supported Goose SDK wrapper. Probe with shell only:

  ```bash
  task --version
  task diagnostics
  ```

  ## Classification

  Use exactly these statuses: `PASS`, `WARN`, `FAIL`, `BLOCKED`, `SKIP`,
  `NOT_CONFIGURED`.

  Overall status:
  - `FAIL` if any required local install/render, recipe validation, or requested
    required endpoint fails.
  - `WARN` if required basics pass but optional MCP/auth/browser capability is
    missing, timed out, or unauthenticated.
  - `PASS` only if all probes selected by scope pass or are explicitly skipped as
    non-required.

  ## Output

  Return this Markdown report:

  ```markdown
  # Goose / MCP Preflight Report

  Generated: <ISO timestamp>
  Scope: <scope>
  Overall: <PASS|WARN|FAIL|BLOCKED>

  ## Summary
  | Area | Status | Evidence | Next action |
  |---|---|---|---|

  ## Details
  [Grouped raw-ish evidence: local tooling, install validation, skills, recipes,
  SDK/MCP probes, subrecipe probe. Keep secrets redacted.]

  ## Recommended Next Actions
  [Prioritized fixes, with commands when safe.]
  ```

  If `write_report=true`, also write the same report to `/tmp` and include the
  path in the final response.

parameters:
  - key: scope
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: "quick"
    description: "Preflight scope: quick, full, or offline."
  - key: write_report
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: "false"
    description: "If true, write a timestamped Markdown report to /tmp."

prompt: |
  Run the ima-goose preflight check.

  Scope: {{ scope }}
  Write report: {{ write_report }}

  Use read-only probes only. Return the structured report and recommended next
  actions.

activities:
  - "Run a read-only Goose and MCP preflight check"
  - "Verify configured recipes, skills, MCP endpoints, and SDK wrappers"
  - "Report which Goose tools are ready, warning, failed, blocked, skipped, or not configured"
